Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Put a #large saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} on to boil for the potatoes. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Halve, peel and finely slice the @red onion{1}. Trim and halve the @Chantenay carrots{225g} lengthways (no need to peel).

Put the pepper and carrots on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle with the @Caribbean style jerk{1} seasoning and season with salt and @pepper{}. Toss to coat and spread out in a single layer. Pop the @caramelised onion sausages{4} on top of the peppers and carrots.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Roast the sausages and veg on the top shelf until the veg are soft and the sausages cooked, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Chop the @potatoes{450g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). When the water is boiling, add the potatoes and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium saucepan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the onion and season with salt. Cook the onion until soft, ~{8-10%minutes}. Add the @water for the sauce{150%ml} and the @chicken stock paste{10%g}, stir to combine then bring to a simmer. Add the @mango chutney{40%g}, stir and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Once the potatoes are ready, drain in a #colander{} and return to the #pot{}. Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @?milk{(a splash)}. Season with salt and pepper and mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}. Stir through the parsley.

> TIP: If the potatoes are cooked before the sausage and veggies, simply put a lid on the pan to
> keep it warm until everything else is ready.

Reheat the gravy if you need to, add a splash of water if it's a bit thick. When the sausages are browned and cooked, and the veggies are soft, remove the baking tray from your oven.

> IMPORTANT: The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Serve the mash with the sausage and veggies with the mango chutney gravy on top. Enjoy!